---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Benchmarks | Ophiolite Charts"
  description="Benchmark direction and methodology for Ophiolite Charts."
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Benchmarks</p>
    <h1>Benchmarking needs to earn trust, not decorate the homepage.</h1>
    <p>
      The benchmark section is part of the commercial story because high-density scientific charting gets judged on concrete behavior. The site should publish repeatable methodology, representative workloads, and clear tradeoffs as this surface matures.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-band">
    <div class="value-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>What to measure</h2>
        <p>Frame stability, interaction latency, viewport updates, and large-model responsiveness across the supported launch families.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>What to avoid</h2>
        <p>Empty headline numbers without workload context, hardware context, or code that another team can inspect and repeat.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>What comes next</h2>
        <p>The benchmark page should evolve into publishable evidence tied to real examples and the actual wrappers that the commercial site recommends.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
